1
00:00:47,777 --> 00:00:51,072
THE APARTMENT JOB

2
00:00:52,156 --> 00:00:54,158
3 YEARS AGO

3
00:00:55,952 --> 00:00:57,745
Good morning, everyone.

4
00:01:01,916 --> 00:01:03,501
-Good morning, sir.
-Hi.

5
00:01:05,128 --> 00:01:06,129
Good morning, sir.

6
00:01:06,212 --> 00:01:07,338
What is this?

7
00:01:07,422 --> 00:01:09,215
We prepared this

8
00:01:09,299 --> 00:01:11,885
because today's VIP guest
is very interested in Korean heritage.

9
00:01:11,968 --> 00:01:15,096
Apparently, he's a Japanese yakuza,
and he's extremely wealthy.

10
00:01:15,180 --> 00:01:17,348
We'll make sure he becomes a regular.

11
00:01:17,432 --> 00:01:18,892
Tadayoshi…

12
00:01:19,976 --> 00:01:21,519
Be careful not to cause any commotion.

13
00:01:21,603 --> 00:01:22,729
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir.

14
00:01:22,812 --> 00:01:23,771
Be careful.

15
00:01:24,272 --> 00:01:25,356
Careful.

16
00:01:48,922 --> 00:01:50,715
This doesn't meet the dress code.

17
00:01:50,798 --> 00:01:51,799
Go back.

18
00:01:51,883 --> 00:01:54,260
We were invited by Mr. Kim.

19
00:01:54,344 --> 00:01:55,637
What is he saying?

20
00:01:57,931 --> 00:01:59,224
You think this is a spa?

21
00:01:59,307 --> 00:02:01,559
This place isn't for just anyone. Leave.

22
00:02:01,643 --> 00:02:04,229
Hey, who do you think we are?

23
00:02:04,312 --> 00:02:05,688
What the hell are you saying?

24
00:02:05,772 --> 00:02:07,023
Just leave.

25
00:02:07,106 --> 00:02:08,483
Mr. Tadayoshi!

26
00:02:08,566 --> 00:02:10,026
He's our VIP.

27
00:02:10,109 --> 00:02:11,694
Welcome!

28
00:02:12,278 --> 00:02:13,363
This way, sir.

29
00:02:13,446 --> 00:02:14,781
This way, please.

30
00:02:14,864 --> 00:02:15,823
Amazing.

31
00:02:16,866 --> 00:02:18,701
Awesome. Hang in there.

32
00:02:25,875 --> 00:02:27,293
We didn't know what you'd like,

33
00:02:27,377 --> 00:02:29,379
but you can assume
we've got everything you'd want.

34
00:02:29,963 --> 00:02:32,548
Roulette, baccarat, hold'em,

35
00:02:32,632 --> 00:02:34,467
go-stop, and poker.

36
00:02:34,550 --> 00:02:36,094
Tell us anything you'd like.

37
00:02:37,512 --> 00:02:39,639
Would you like some tea first, sir?

38
00:02:58,908 --> 00:03:00,910
Tadayoshi.

39
00:03:01,494 --> 00:03:02,787
I missed you.

40
00:03:02,870 --> 00:03:05,707
You won't make it back to Japan alive.

41
00:03:05,790 --> 00:03:08,292
Ichigaro, you followed me
all the way here?

42
00:03:08,376 --> 00:03:09,252
Fine.

43
00:03:10,086 --> 00:03:11,421
Let's end this here.

44
00:03:13,631 --> 00:03:14,757
Get him!

45
00:03:25,226 --> 00:03:26,102
What do we do?

46
00:03:51,085 --> 00:03:53,254
Hey! Kill that jerk first!

47
00:04:32,043 --> 00:04:32,877
Sayonara!

48
00:04:47,850 --> 00:04:48,684
Stop!

49
00:05:09,414 --> 00:05:10,998
We don't even know each other.

50
00:05:11,582 --> 00:05:13,000
Why did you save me?

51
00:05:13,751 --> 00:05:15,753
Because you're my customer.

52
00:05:26,264 --> 00:05:27,932
From now on,

53
00:05:28,891 --> 00:05:30,435
we're brothers.

54
00:05:31,853 --> 00:05:33,312
I promise

55
00:05:33,396 --> 00:05:35,022
to repay you someday.

56
00:05:43,531 --> 00:05:48,786
THE APARTMENT JOB

57
00:05:54,041 --> 00:05:55,710
-Thank you.
-Hello.

58
00:05:55,793 --> 00:05:57,128
Hello.

59
00:06:02,592 --> 00:06:04,635
I'm aching all over.

60
00:06:05,136 --> 00:06:07,972
You're the building rep now.
How long are we going to do this?

61
00:06:10,224 --> 00:06:12,935
You're the one who played a key role
in getting me elected.

62
00:06:13,519 --> 00:06:14,896
What do you mean?

63
00:06:18,482 --> 00:06:19,942
Hey, why are you running?

64
00:06:20,026 --> 00:06:22,361
I can run 100 meters in 10 seconds.
Don't you dare.

65
00:06:23,362 --> 00:06:24,864
Why were you chasing after us?

66
00:06:24,947 --> 00:06:26,532
You startled us.

67
00:06:28,242 --> 00:06:29,619
What's your deal?

68
00:06:29,702 --> 00:06:31,037
What?

69
00:06:31,579 --> 00:06:32,705
You took the video.

70
00:06:32,788 --> 00:06:34,665
Did you even get permission to upload it?

71
00:06:34,749 --> 00:06:36,834
Violating portrait rights, defamation,

72
00:06:36,918 --> 00:06:38,544
and spreading false information

73
00:06:38,628 --> 00:06:40,588
may result in up to two years
of imprisonment

74
00:06:40,671 --> 00:06:42,131
or a fine of up to five million won.

75
00:06:42,215 --> 00:06:43,966
Whatever. I'm a juvenile--

76
00:06:44,050 --> 00:06:46,844
Don't start with that
"juvenile offender" bullshit.

77
00:06:47,345 --> 00:06:48,471
Guys.

78
00:06:49,180 --> 00:06:51,182
You don't look anywhere

79
00:06:51,265 --> 00:06:54,435
near the age of 14.

80
00:07:01,108 --> 00:07:03,277
This contains the truth about last night.

81
00:07:03,361 --> 00:07:05,404
I trust you to bring the truth to light.

82
00:07:07,531 --> 00:07:09,367
I heard everything
from the head of security.

83
00:07:10,368 --> 00:07:11,410
Thank you.

84
00:07:13,871 --> 00:07:17,041
It's not like I fabricated anything.

85
00:07:17,792 --> 00:07:21,254
I didn't have any other intentions.
You know I can't stand failure.

86
00:07:21,754 --> 00:07:22,964
Of course.

87
00:07:24,840 --> 00:07:27,176
I'll just do this
until I become the president.

88
00:07:27,677 --> 00:07:29,887
What will you do after that, then?

89
00:07:30,638 --> 00:07:33,933
I'll just let the delivery trucks enter
with my authority.

90
00:07:37,019 --> 00:07:40,022
Breaking news.
Oman has been officially approved

91
00:07:40,106 --> 00:07:42,316
for the new town project.

92
00:07:42,400 --> 00:07:45,820
Many are describing this
as an unprecedented decision.

93
00:07:45,903 --> 00:07:49,782
The final approval of Oman New Town,
which had been excluded

94
00:07:49,865 --> 00:07:52,618
from the list of candidates
for the new town project,

95
00:07:52,702 --> 00:07:55,663
came as a surprise to the industry.

96
00:07:55,746 --> 00:07:57,415
-However, Oman…
-Let's turn it off.

97
00:08:01,127 --> 00:08:01,961
It seems

98
00:08:03,004 --> 00:08:05,798
the assembly members
did their job right this time.

99
00:08:06,382 --> 00:08:08,843
My money finally paid off.

100
00:08:08,926 --> 00:08:10,094
Isn't this nice?

101
00:08:10,678 --> 00:08:12,597
Those who need money get paid,

102
00:08:12,680 --> 00:08:15,391
and they do their job properly in return.

103
00:08:15,474 --> 00:08:17,810
How fair is that?

104
00:08:19,312 --> 00:08:23,691
It's about time our association president
earned his keep as well.

105
00:08:23,774 --> 00:08:24,775
What is he up to?

106
00:08:27,028 --> 00:08:29,155
PRESIDENT SEO GANG-WON

107
00:08:31,240 --> 00:08:32,825
Yes, sir.

108
00:08:32,908 --> 00:08:35,453
I hear Park Hae-kang
became the building rep.

109
00:08:35,953 --> 00:08:37,955
This is so fun.

110
00:08:38,039 --> 00:08:39,707
I found him quite interesting.

111
00:08:40,291 --> 00:08:41,459
Well, I…

112
00:08:43,252 --> 00:08:44,378
Yes…

113
00:08:44,462 --> 00:08:45,504
But President Seo,

114
00:08:45,588 --> 00:08:48,466
this has to stop at just being fun.

115
00:08:48,549 --> 00:08:49,842
You understand, don't you?

116
00:08:49,925 --> 00:08:50,843
Well…

117
00:08:52,053 --> 00:08:53,387
Yes, sir.

118
00:08:53,471 --> 00:08:54,764
Then first,

119
00:08:55,348 --> 00:08:57,642
remove the restrictions
on the delivery trucks.

120
00:08:58,726 --> 00:09:02,730
But you're the one
who ordered those restrictions.

121
00:09:02,813 --> 00:09:05,191
You said they were ruining
the landscaping.

122
00:09:05,274 --> 00:09:06,859
Well, Park Hae-kang

123
00:09:07,652 --> 00:09:10,571
is getting on my nerves
more than the ruined landscaping.

124
00:09:11,572 --> 00:09:12,573
Got that?

125
00:09:21,290 --> 00:09:22,124
Mr. Kim.

126
00:09:23,459 --> 00:09:26,379
Maybe it's because I'm really petty,

127
00:09:26,962 --> 00:09:29,799
but I just can't stand anyone
being called a hero

128
00:09:29,882 --> 00:09:31,509
in my apartment complex.

129
00:09:33,302 --> 00:09:34,887
But this is bad.

130
00:09:36,389 --> 00:09:38,015
Park Hae-kang

131
00:09:39,934 --> 00:09:41,852
is becoming quite interesting.

132
00:09:44,730 --> 00:09:45,856
Enjoy.

133
00:09:45,940 --> 00:09:46,857
Thank you.

134
00:09:46,941 --> 00:09:50,403
You can even make
black bean noodles at home? Amazing.

135
00:09:50,486 --> 00:09:52,655
-I thought it was delivery.
-This is nothing.

136
00:09:53,322 --> 00:09:55,700
-Eat up, Gyeong-buk.
-Okay.

137
00:09:55,783 --> 00:09:58,369
You guys should eat up
to be ready for afternoon deliveries.

138
00:09:58,452 --> 00:09:59,453
-Yes, Boss.
-Yes, Boss.

139
00:10:01,163 --> 00:10:03,124
Eat up, son.

140
00:10:05,751 --> 00:10:07,253
It's too big.

141
00:10:08,546 --> 00:10:09,422
Is it too big?

142
00:10:11,757 --> 00:10:12,591
Gosh…

143
00:10:14,593 --> 00:10:15,511
I'll cut it for you.

144
00:10:15,594 --> 00:10:17,138
You're high-maintenance.

145
00:10:23,227 --> 00:10:24,687
FACILITY MANAGER

146
00:10:25,813 --> 00:10:27,523
What's the occasion, Mr. Choi?

147
00:10:27,606 --> 00:10:30,234
You don't have to make deliveries anymore.

148
00:10:31,026 --> 00:10:32,319
What?

149
00:10:32,403 --> 00:10:36,657
It doesn't look good to have
packages piled up at the entrance,

150
00:10:36,741 --> 00:10:39,827
and residents have been filing complaints.

151
00:10:39,910 --> 00:10:43,247
So we decided to let
the delivery trucks enter again.

152
00:10:43,330 --> 00:10:45,791
I just needed to tell you that. Bye, then.

153
00:10:51,380 --> 00:10:52,673
That was the facility manager.

154
00:10:52,757 --> 00:10:55,384
We don't have to do deliveries anymore.

155
00:10:55,468 --> 00:10:57,094
They're letting the trucks enter.

156
00:10:57,178 --> 00:10:58,763
Why? That's sudden.

157
00:10:59,263 --> 00:11:01,390
I don't know.
He said there were complaints.

158
00:11:01,474 --> 00:11:02,892
What complaints?

159
00:11:02,975 --> 00:11:06,061
I thought everyone was happy
with us delivering their packages.

160
00:11:06,645 --> 00:11:09,148
Well, if residents file complaints,

161
00:11:09,231 --> 00:11:11,358
the management office has no other choice.

162
00:11:11,442 --> 00:11:15,196
I guess some sensitive residents
were complaining again.

163
00:11:15,279 --> 00:11:16,989
Oh dear.

164
00:11:17,072 --> 00:11:20,159
But I guess we won't have
to make deliveries anymore.

165
00:11:23,162 --> 00:11:24,246
This is so good.

166
00:11:24,330 --> 00:11:26,415
You seem pretty excited.

167
00:11:26,499 --> 00:11:27,583
Is it just me?

168
00:11:30,002 --> 00:11:32,922
Couldn't you sense
the disappointment in my voice?

169
00:11:33,005 --> 00:11:36,884
I'm worried about
how you'll build your reputation now.

170
00:11:36,967 --> 00:11:40,596
But isn't our boss already quite famous
within the apartment complex now?

171
00:11:40,679 --> 00:11:44,058
He's right. No need to worry.
You've already built quite a reputation.

172
00:11:44,808 --> 00:11:46,810
I have to win over 9,800 households.

173
00:11:49,563 --> 00:11:51,690
Reputation alone won't be enough.

174
00:11:54,068 --> 00:11:55,986
I need something with more impact.

175
00:11:58,572 --> 00:11:59,406
Mr. Park.

176
00:12:00,074 --> 00:12:03,285
Stop acting all cool here and go outside.

177
00:12:04,286 --> 00:12:05,454
You two, go together.

178
00:12:05,955 --> 00:12:07,373
-Me too?
-Yes.

179
00:12:07,456 --> 00:12:10,000
Just go and greet all the residents.

180
00:12:10,584 --> 00:12:14,463
The basics of an election
are meeting voters in person.

181
00:12:18,926 --> 00:12:21,303
Don't you have a plan?
Are we just going to keep walking?

182
00:12:22,263 --> 00:12:23,347
I'm thinking.

183
00:12:24,348 --> 00:12:27,518
Let me give you some advice.

184
00:12:27,601 --> 00:12:29,937
Just walking like this
won't be of any use.

185
00:12:30,020 --> 00:12:32,314
You already have quite a reputation,

186
00:12:32,398 --> 00:12:34,984
so you should use that
to get more people on your side.

187
00:12:35,067 --> 00:12:36,068
My side?

188
00:12:36,151 --> 00:12:37,695
Like a faction.

189
00:12:37,778 --> 00:12:38,988
Or a support base.

190
00:12:41,865 --> 00:12:42,866
That's good.

191
00:12:43,742 --> 00:12:45,035
Let's get some supporters.

192
00:12:46,453 --> 00:12:48,789
Then let's head over there.

193
00:12:48,872 --> 00:12:50,583
There are lots of women gathered there.

194
00:12:50,666 --> 00:12:53,002
You can greet them
and have some coffee with them.

195
00:12:53,502 --> 00:12:54,336
Come on.

196
00:12:54,420 --> 00:12:56,255
My legs hurt from walking so much.

197
00:12:58,549 --> 00:13:01,302
-Congratulations.
-Congratulations.

198
00:13:01,385 --> 00:13:04,263
I can't believe you became
the building representative.

199
00:13:04,346 --> 00:13:06,140
It's nothing to be congratulated for.

200
00:13:06,223 --> 00:13:08,434
Why not? It's so cool.

201
00:13:08,517 --> 00:13:10,853
You're our representative.

202
00:13:10,936 --> 00:13:11,812
Right.

203
00:13:11,895 --> 00:13:14,857
You all know I was the sole candidate.

204
00:13:14,940 --> 00:13:17,067
In any case, I'm so relieved

205
00:13:17,151 --> 00:13:19,236
that you're our building rep.

206
00:13:19,320 --> 00:13:22,031
We can properly have our voices heard now.

207
00:13:22,114 --> 00:13:24,158
You should run
for association president as well.

208
00:13:24,241 --> 00:13:25,868
We'll support you all the way.

209
00:13:25,951 --> 00:13:27,077
-You should.
-Really.

210
00:13:28,329 --> 00:13:29,872
Don't be silly.

211
00:13:41,008 --> 00:13:42,176
Did you run for building rep?

212
00:13:42,926 --> 00:13:44,386
Yes.

213
00:13:44,470 --> 00:13:46,430
Did you see? I got elected.

214
00:13:47,139 --> 00:13:48,557
It's basically volunteer work.

215
00:13:48,641 --> 00:13:51,727
It's nothing difficult,
so you don't have to worry.

216
00:13:51,810 --> 00:13:53,187
Quit this, right now.

217
00:13:54,063 --> 00:13:54,897
What?

218
00:13:54,980 --> 00:13:56,148
Don't do it.

219
00:13:56,231 --> 00:13:59,985
I don't want you to do anything, honey.

220
00:14:00,069 --> 00:14:03,405
I just want you to sit still,
like a flower.

221
00:14:03,489 --> 00:14:06,033
Like a pretty houseplant. Okay?

222
00:14:09,870 --> 00:14:11,288
BUILDING REP ELECTION RESULTS NOTICE

223
00:14:14,249 --> 00:14:15,334
Yun-jo.

224
00:14:15,417 --> 00:14:16,627
Are you okay?

225
00:14:17,378 --> 00:14:19,463
I'm fine.

226
00:14:19,546 --> 00:14:23,008
Since we're on the topic, we should…

227
00:14:23,092 --> 00:14:24,677
Oh, it's that guy with the crazy kick.

228
00:14:24,760 --> 00:14:26,553
From District 4!

229
00:14:29,515 --> 00:14:31,141
Look how handsome he is.

230
00:14:31,225 --> 00:14:32,142
He's coming this way.

231
00:14:32,226 --> 00:14:35,062
He's so handsome. He looks like an actor.

232
00:14:35,646 --> 00:14:38,607
He looks like a model.

233
00:14:44,029 --> 00:14:45,114
Mr. Park.

234
00:14:46,115 --> 00:14:47,741
-Hello.
-Hello.

235
00:14:47,825 --> 00:14:50,536
Congratulations on getting elected.

236
00:14:50,619 --> 00:14:52,371
I should've lived in District 4.

237
00:14:52,454 --> 00:14:53,789
Me too.

238
00:14:53,872 --> 00:14:55,916
Thank you. I'm the guy who did that kick.

239
00:14:56,875 --> 00:14:58,085
Oh my gosh!

240
00:15:00,421 --> 00:15:01,672
The delivery hero.

241
00:15:01,755 --> 00:15:03,382
-A hero.
-It was so convenient.

242
00:15:03,465 --> 00:15:05,217
I don't know why I did that.

243
00:15:06,385 --> 00:15:08,637
I'm Park Hae-kang,
District 4's representative.

244
00:15:14,852 --> 00:15:15,853
Honey.

245
00:15:17,730 --> 00:15:19,356
I guess she can't hear me.

246
00:15:20,190 --> 00:15:21,525
Where the heck did he go?

247
00:15:22,276 --> 00:15:24,153
-Honey.
-"Honey"?

248
00:15:24,236 --> 00:15:25,362
That's so sweet.

249
00:15:26,530 --> 00:15:27,740
Ha-ri!

250
00:15:27,823 --> 00:15:28,866
"Ha-ri"?

251
00:15:36,165 --> 00:15:37,875
Hey, honey.

252
00:15:39,752 --> 00:15:40,836
Goodness.

253
00:15:40,919 --> 00:15:42,254
He even ran over to her.

254
00:15:42,337 --> 00:15:43,630
-That's so sweet.
-He's so sweet.

255
00:15:45,799 --> 00:15:47,926
-Hello.
-Hello.

256
00:15:48,010 --> 00:15:49,303
Isn't my wife beautiful?

257
00:15:49,386 --> 00:15:50,304
"Beautiful"?

258
00:15:51,346 --> 00:15:52,222
I rarely hear that.

259
00:15:52,306 --> 00:15:53,307
They're so sweet.

260
00:15:53,390 --> 00:15:55,267
-Do you want to sit here, honey?
-Sure.

261
00:15:55,350 --> 00:15:56,393
They look good together.

262
00:15:56,477 --> 00:15:57,478
It's like they're dating.

263
00:15:57,561 --> 00:15:59,104
-Right?
-They're so sweet.

264
00:15:59,188 --> 00:16:00,773
You must be newlyweds.

265
00:16:00,856 --> 00:16:02,357
You're so romantic.

266
00:16:02,441 --> 00:16:04,568
How long have you been married?

267
00:16:04,651 --> 00:16:05,861
-Eight…
-Six…

268
00:16:08,655 --> 00:16:10,449
-Has it been eight years already?
-Yes.

269
00:16:11,033 --> 00:16:13,952
I meant six years
after registering our marriage.

270
00:16:14,036 --> 00:16:15,079
How old is your kid?

271
00:16:15,162 --> 00:16:16,371
-Seven.
-Six.

272
00:16:18,332 --> 00:16:20,709
-He's six in international age.
-That's right.

273
00:16:20,793 --> 00:16:23,212
-Right, we use international age now.
-It's confusing.

274
00:16:23,295 --> 00:16:24,379
It's pretty confusing.

275
00:16:25,005 --> 00:16:27,257
Mr. Park, you're so handsome.

276
00:16:28,383 --> 00:16:30,219
I hear that often.

277
00:16:31,637 --> 00:16:34,181
But how did you two meet?

278
00:16:41,730 --> 00:16:43,482
It must have been somewhere embarrassing.

279
00:16:43,565 --> 00:16:44,691
A nightclub?

280
00:16:44,775 --> 00:16:45,818
-A nightclub?
-Is it?

281
00:16:46,568 --> 00:16:48,946
-That's ridiculous.
-I'm tearing up.

282
00:16:52,157 --> 00:16:53,992
First encounter, library

283
00:16:54,076 --> 00:16:55,661
First kiss, under a street light

284
00:16:55,744 --> 00:16:58,622
Fateful encounter
At a book club after-party

285
00:17:01,125 --> 00:17:04,128
Got it? We fell in love at first sight

286
00:17:04,211 --> 00:17:05,712
and felt that it was fate.

287
00:17:05,796 --> 00:17:06,672
Don't forget that.

288
00:17:07,881 --> 00:17:11,426
It's quite hard to believe
that I'd fall for you at first sight,

289
00:17:12,219 --> 00:17:13,929
but it's a safe story.

290
00:17:14,012 --> 00:17:14,972
Let's go with it.

291
00:17:15,055 --> 00:17:16,306
Hey.

292
00:17:16,390 --> 00:17:17,266
Your bonus.

293
00:17:18,225 --> 00:17:20,644
You worked hard delivering packages,

294
00:17:20,727 --> 00:17:22,396
and you came up with our backstory,

295
00:17:22,479 --> 00:17:24,731
so I'll give you a bonus.

296
00:17:24,815 --> 00:17:25,649
A bonus?

297
00:17:30,988 --> 00:17:33,407
I have my first
building rep meeting today,

298
00:17:33,490 --> 00:17:35,742
so take Gyeong-buk

299
00:17:35,826 --> 00:17:38,036
and put on a good mom act.

300
00:17:39,621 --> 00:17:40,497
Mom?

301
00:17:43,167 --> 00:17:46,086
Mom, I feel like I'm flying.

302
00:17:46,170 --> 00:17:48,338
No, you can't fly.

303
00:17:48,422 --> 00:17:49,756
I know that.

304
00:17:49,840 --> 00:17:51,216
I just meant this is nice.

305
00:17:51,300 --> 00:17:52,134
Right.

306
00:17:59,266 --> 00:18:00,934
-Ma'am.
-What?

307
00:18:01,560 --> 00:18:02,644
Isn't my mom pretty?

308
00:18:03,645 --> 00:18:05,564
Oh… Right.

309
00:18:05,647 --> 00:18:06,857
You're pretty too,

310
00:18:07,608 --> 00:18:09,401
but I think my mom's prettier.

311
00:18:10,527 --> 00:18:12,613
She's the prettiest
in our apartment complex.

312
00:18:12,696 --> 00:18:14,323
Stop that. Sorry.

313
00:18:15,032 --> 00:18:17,117
I guess you wanted to brag about your mom.

314
00:18:17,201 --> 00:18:19,912
Yes. Mom's really good at deboning fish,

315
00:18:19,995 --> 00:18:23,207
and she's super strong,
so she can carry heavy packages.

316
00:18:23,290 --> 00:18:25,959
And… my uncles all listen to her well.

317
00:18:27,002 --> 00:18:28,337
Even her name is pretty.

318
00:18:28,962 --> 00:18:31,673
Thank you, my son.

319
00:18:32,841 --> 00:18:34,384
Let's keep swinging.

320
00:18:36,595 --> 00:18:37,888
Bye.

321
00:18:44,311 --> 00:18:45,771
Mr. Park.

322
00:18:45,854 --> 00:18:47,898
Wow, you're dressed nicely.

323
00:18:47,981 --> 00:18:49,483
You'll really stand out.

324
00:18:50,067 --> 00:18:52,319
-Is it too much?
-It's way too much.

325
00:18:52,402 --> 00:18:54,821
But you have a handsome face,

326
00:18:54,905 --> 00:18:57,574
so it might be effective
to use that as a weapon.

327
00:18:57,658 --> 00:18:58,700
Never mind that.

328
00:18:59,534 --> 00:19:01,912
I've never been
to a building rep meeting before.

329
00:19:01,995 --> 00:19:03,705
Is there anything
I need to be cautious of?

330
00:19:03,789 --> 00:19:04,915
Of course there is.

331
00:19:04,998 --> 00:19:07,751
That's why I prepared something for you.

332
00:19:07,834 --> 00:19:09,044
Sit down for a second.

333
00:19:14,508 --> 00:19:15,509
See this?

334
00:19:15,592 --> 00:19:16,927
Reappointed, reappointed,

335
00:19:17,010 --> 00:19:18,512
reappointed, reappointed.

336
00:19:18,595 --> 00:19:20,180
-Reappointed.
-So what?

337
00:19:23,308 --> 00:19:26,395
It means there's already
an established network in place.

338
00:19:26,979 --> 00:19:28,939
Look, all these people were reappointed.

339
00:19:29,815 --> 00:19:32,192
They've already made deals
among themselves.

340
00:19:32,693 --> 00:19:33,568
Let's see.

341
00:19:34,194 --> 00:19:35,988
He's the association president,

342
00:19:36,071 --> 00:19:37,489
and he's been reappointed too.

343
00:19:37,572 --> 00:19:40,075
So it's pretty obvious.

344
00:19:40,659 --> 00:19:42,327
This guy is the leader,

345
00:19:42,411 --> 00:19:44,579
and the others here will be flanking him

346
00:19:44,663 --> 00:19:46,957
like his bodyguards.

347
00:19:47,582 --> 00:19:50,335
There's already a close-knit cartel

348
00:19:50,419 --> 00:19:52,296
in this association.

349
00:19:55,424 --> 00:19:57,134
This won't be easy.

350
00:19:57,217 --> 00:20:00,470
You should brace yourself.
It's going to be a very lonely battle.

351
00:20:03,890 --> 00:20:06,560
DISTRICT 1, SEO GANG-WON

352
00:20:06,643 --> 00:20:08,937
TRUE VALUE STATE
4TH-TERM RESIDENTS' ASSOCIATION MEETING

353
00:20:09,021 --> 00:20:10,897
-It's been a while.
-Hello.

354
00:20:11,815 --> 00:20:12,983
Welcome.

355
00:20:14,526 --> 00:20:15,902
Welcome.

356
00:20:16,737 --> 00:20:22,034
Since this is the first meeting
for the new term of building reps,

357
00:20:22,117 --> 00:20:23,910
I'll wrap up the announcements here.

358
00:20:23,994 --> 00:20:26,663
We have
the most important agenda item left.

359
00:20:27,247 --> 00:20:29,541
We all know the election
for president is coming up.

360
00:20:30,292 --> 00:20:31,335
-Yes.
-Yes.

361
00:20:31,418 --> 00:20:35,672
Mr. Seo Gang-won,
who is our current association president,

362
00:20:35,756 --> 00:20:40,218
has decided to run for the position again.

363
00:20:40,302 --> 00:20:41,261
Round of applause.

364
00:20:41,345 --> 00:20:42,679
Round of applause!

365
00:20:49,728 --> 00:20:53,857
We'll feel so reassured
if you continue as our president.

366
00:20:54,566 --> 00:20:56,193
She's one of his guards.

367
00:20:56,276 --> 00:21:00,030
Who else would be able
to take on such a difficult task?

368
00:21:00,113 --> 00:21:01,156
Exactly.

369
00:21:01,239 --> 00:21:02,324
And he's one too.

370
00:21:02,407 --> 00:21:04,159
I'm asking just in case.

371
00:21:04,242 --> 00:21:06,078
No one else is running, right?

372
00:21:06,161 --> 00:21:08,663
-No.
-No, sir.

373
00:21:13,126 --> 00:21:14,628
I will run as well.

374
00:21:15,462 --> 00:21:16,588
He's running…

375
00:21:17,464 --> 00:21:18,298
What?

376
00:21:18,382 --> 00:21:23,303
All right. Mr. Park Hae-kang
from District 4 will be running too.

377
00:21:23,387 --> 00:21:25,555
Is there anyone else?

378
00:21:31,478 --> 00:21:35,315
Just to be sure, Mr. Park Hae-kang,

379
00:21:35,399 --> 00:21:39,403
are you really going to run
for residents' association president?

380
00:21:39,486 --> 00:21:41,279
It won't be an easy job.

381
00:21:44,116 --> 00:21:45,992
Yes, I am.

382
00:21:48,370 --> 00:21:51,248
You're too young to be doing that.

383
00:21:51,331 --> 00:21:53,792
We won't vote for you
just because you're handsome.

384
00:21:53,875 --> 00:21:56,294
It's better for the former president
to continue.

385
00:21:56,378 --> 00:21:58,422
Not just anyone can do it.

386
00:21:58,505 --> 00:21:59,881
Right.

387
00:21:59,965 --> 00:22:01,633
Will it be okay to just sit and watch?

388
00:22:01,716 --> 00:22:05,178
I didn't expect Park Hae-kang
to run for president.

389
00:22:05,262 --> 00:22:08,306
President Seo,
Park Hae-kang is quite popular.

390
00:22:08,390 --> 00:22:11,685
He was called a delivery hero,
and with that kicking incident,

391
00:22:11,768 --> 00:22:13,603
he built quite a reputation.

392
00:22:13,687 --> 00:22:15,439
Shouldn't we do something as well?

393
00:22:15,522 --> 00:22:16,440
He's right.

394
00:22:16,523 --> 00:22:19,359
The residents will just vote
for the popular candidate.

395
00:22:19,443 --> 00:22:22,362
If Park Hae-kang really becomes
the president, it'll be a disaster.

396
00:22:22,446 --> 00:22:23,989
He could actually win at this rate.

397
00:22:24,072 --> 00:22:25,282
-Geez!
-Come on.

398
00:22:28,785 --> 00:22:30,328
CANDIDATE REGISTRATION FORM

399
00:22:30,412 --> 00:22:31,955
Any campaign pledge ideas?

400
00:22:33,123 --> 00:22:34,291
My opponent is President Seo.

401
00:22:34,374 --> 00:22:35,959
He's aiming for a fourth term.

402
00:22:36,042 --> 00:22:37,252
He's a strong opponent,

403
00:22:37,335 --> 00:22:40,130
so we need a bold pledge
that will grab everyone's attention.

404
00:22:43,049 --> 00:22:46,261
Last time, you said you'd make
a "very good apartment complex."

405
00:22:46,344 --> 00:22:49,055
This time, go for
a "very, very good apartment complex."

406
00:22:52,517 --> 00:22:54,769
Why don't you just say
"fantastic and amazing" instead?

407
00:22:54,853 --> 00:22:57,147
Are you kidding me?

408
00:22:57,731 --> 00:23:00,150
Campaign pledges don't mean anything.

409
00:23:00,233 --> 00:23:02,360
Don't you remember
class president elections?

410
00:23:02,444 --> 00:23:04,237
Kids didn't vote based on the pledges.

411
00:23:04,321 --> 00:23:07,657
They voted for candidates
who were handsome, popular, smart,

412
00:23:08,617 --> 00:23:09,701
or ate well.

413
00:23:09,784 --> 00:23:10,619
Kids like that.

414
00:23:10,702 --> 00:23:13,580
Nobody actually cares about the pledges.

415
00:23:13,663 --> 00:23:17,042
Boss, as the Lizard said,
I think you can write anything down.

416
00:23:17,125 --> 00:23:18,585
I believe he has a point.

417
00:23:18,668 --> 00:23:21,379
It's not like you got elected
because of your pledge.

418
00:23:30,847 --> 00:23:32,057
CANDIDATE PROFILE
PARK HAE-KANG

419
00:23:33,225 --> 00:23:35,018
IF I'VE TAKEN ANY BRIBES,
I'LL DONATE MY APARTMENT

420
00:23:35,101 --> 00:23:37,229
He'll donate his apartment?

421
00:23:37,312 --> 00:23:40,398
I know he's desperate to become
the president, but this is crazy.

422
00:23:50,367 --> 00:23:52,369
Park Hae-kang…

423
00:23:52,452 --> 00:23:54,704
He's the type who'll succeed in anything.

424
00:23:54,788 --> 00:23:56,373
He's bold.

425
00:23:56,456 --> 00:23:57,874
Now that's a real man.

426
00:24:01,419 --> 00:24:03,880
But I can't let him succeed

427
00:24:03,964 --> 00:24:05,924
in my apartment complex.

428
00:24:13,431 --> 00:24:14,516
Someone's coming!

429
00:24:14,599 --> 00:24:15,767
Gyeong-nam!

430
00:24:20,105 --> 00:24:21,940
-Hello.
-Hello.

431
00:24:22,023 --> 00:24:22,857
I'll take that.

432
00:24:23,900 --> 00:24:24,985
There's a lot, though.

433
00:24:25,068 --> 00:24:27,487
We should help each other as neighbors.

434
00:24:28,071 --> 00:24:30,448
-Thank you.
-Have a great day.

435
00:24:31,866 --> 00:24:33,368
-Plastic…
-Hello.

436
00:24:34,035 --> 00:24:35,370
How is your baby?

437
00:24:36,746 --> 00:24:38,999
Hello. Let me take that.

438
00:24:40,417 --> 00:24:41,835
I have hands too.

439
00:24:42,585 --> 00:24:43,545
It's nothing special.

440
00:24:43,628 --> 00:24:45,505
You're making such a fuss.

441
00:24:45,588 --> 00:24:46,423
Where is it?

442
00:24:47,048 --> 00:24:48,550
The plastic bin's over there…

443
00:24:55,807 --> 00:24:57,142
It's fine!

444
00:24:57,225 --> 00:24:58,768
What's with you?

445
00:25:07,235 --> 00:25:09,195
-Thank you for everything.
-Sure.

446
00:25:20,832 --> 00:25:23,376
Is it already time
to discuss a contract renewal?

447
00:25:24,085 --> 00:25:26,338
That's actually why we dropped by.

448
00:25:26,421 --> 00:25:30,508
How will you choose
the contractor this time, sir?

449
00:25:30,592 --> 00:25:31,676
What do you mean?

450
00:25:31,760 --> 00:25:34,054
We'll go through a fair bidding process.

451
00:25:34,137 --> 00:25:35,347
Sir.

452
00:25:36,890 --> 00:25:40,810
I'm sure you can easily pull
some strings for this.

453
00:25:40,894 --> 00:25:42,854
I don't have any power.

454
00:25:42,937 --> 00:25:43,897
Come on.

455
00:25:48,360 --> 00:25:49,402
I was just kidding.

456
00:25:49,486 --> 00:25:52,906
Of course I can pull
a few strings for you guys.

457
00:25:53,782 --> 00:25:55,075
Thank you, sir.

458
00:26:00,080 --> 00:26:02,665
I'm pretty sure it's him.

459
00:26:02,749 --> 00:26:03,666
What?

460
00:26:03,750 --> 00:26:05,627
His name's Park Hae-kang.

461
00:26:05,710 --> 00:26:07,212
It really is him.

462
00:26:07,295 --> 00:26:09,297
No wonder he seemed familiar.

463
00:26:09,381 --> 00:26:10,507
Hang on.

464
00:26:11,674 --> 00:26:13,593
-Do you know him?
-Yes.

465
00:26:13,676 --> 00:26:16,388
He was the boss of the Oasis Gang.

466
00:26:17,097 --> 00:26:18,515
The Oasis Gang?

467
00:26:18,598 --> 00:26:19,974
Yes.

468
00:26:20,058 --> 00:26:22,519
I wondered how he was living
after retirement.

469
00:26:22,602 --> 00:26:23,436
What a surprise.

470
00:26:23,520 --> 00:26:24,813
But this guy

471
00:26:24,896 --> 00:26:27,232
must have earned quite some money
to be living here.

472
00:26:27,315 --> 00:26:28,566
Right.

473
00:26:28,650 --> 00:26:30,485
-Are you sure about this?
-Yes.

474
00:26:34,322 --> 00:26:35,949
All done.

475
00:26:36,825 --> 00:26:38,535
Today was the toughest.

476
00:26:40,328 --> 00:26:41,663
What's this?

477
00:26:43,039 --> 00:26:44,666
An urgent meeting?

478
00:26:45,667 --> 00:26:47,252
The building reps have to attend?

479
00:26:48,670 --> 00:26:50,588
This is the management office.

480
00:26:50,672 --> 00:26:53,299
Today's building representative meeting

481
00:26:53,383 --> 00:26:57,637
will include an important agenda item
regarding the election,

482
00:26:57,720 --> 00:27:01,808
so it will be broadcast
for all households to watch.

483
00:27:01,891 --> 00:27:03,435
We will appreciate your attention.

484
00:27:03,518 --> 00:27:06,438
-They're broadcasting the meeting?
-Thank you.

485
00:27:06,521 --> 00:27:07,856
Is something going on?

486
00:27:08,481 --> 00:27:11,651
They wouldn't do such a thing
unless it's really important.

487
00:27:11,734 --> 00:27:12,569
Do I have to go?

488
00:27:12,652 --> 00:27:13,987
Of course you do.

489
00:27:14,070 --> 00:27:15,488
You should get ready, Boss.

490
00:27:18,283 --> 00:27:22,162
All right. Let's begin
the building representatives' meeting.

491
00:27:22,912 --> 00:27:23,997
What's the urgent issue?

492
00:27:24,080 --> 00:27:27,417
The president will explain it now.

493
00:27:30,879 --> 00:27:36,259
Thank you all for attending
when you must be busy.

494
00:27:36,342 --> 00:27:39,596
Our boss really stands out
among all those people.

495
00:27:41,014 --> 00:27:43,475
That's because of his flashy jacket.

496
00:27:44,476 --> 00:27:46,269
He's the youngest.

497
00:27:47,020 --> 00:27:51,316
We called this emergency meeting today

498
00:27:51,399 --> 00:27:52,525
because the residents

499
00:27:52,609 --> 00:27:54,152
-have the right to know.
-"Soccer."

500
00:27:54,235 --> 00:27:58,031
-A very troubling incident has occurred.
-Oh my.

501
00:27:58,114 --> 00:28:03,244
-Something outrageous has happened here.
-He's so handsome.

502
00:28:03,328 --> 00:28:07,499
Among the building representatives
who were elected this time,

503
00:28:07,582 --> 00:28:11,419
there's someone
who submitted false credentials.

504
00:28:19,886 --> 00:28:22,263
What's with that annoying smirk?

505
00:28:22,347 --> 00:28:25,350
Who submitted false credentials?

506
00:28:25,433 --> 00:28:28,019
If someone really did,
that's a huge problem.

507
00:28:28,102 --> 00:28:29,604
Tell us who it is.

508
00:28:29,687 --> 00:28:34,108
I apologize once again
for having to bring up

509
00:28:34,192 --> 00:28:35,777
such an uncomfortable matter.

510
00:28:35,860 --> 00:28:37,445
But Mr. Park Hae-kang,

511
00:28:38,488 --> 00:28:41,991
I heard you were the boss
of the Oasis Gang,

512
00:28:42,075 --> 00:28:45,912
which was a nationwide gang

513
00:28:45,995 --> 00:28:47,747
that was even on the news.

514
00:28:47,831 --> 00:28:49,249
Gosh, it's hot!

515
00:28:50,124 --> 00:28:52,627
He got caught.

516
00:28:53,253 --> 00:28:55,046
You…

517
00:28:57,340 --> 00:28:59,092
used to be the boss of a gang.

518
00:28:59,175 --> 00:29:03,596
Why did you hide that fact from everyone?

519
00:29:04,848 --> 00:29:06,391
-A gang?
-A gang?

520
00:29:06,474 --> 00:29:07,392
A gang?

521
00:29:07,475 --> 00:29:09,185
A gang? Goodness.

522
00:29:10,311 --> 00:29:12,939
Goodness gracious.

523
00:29:13,022 --> 00:29:14,065
Oh my gosh.

524
00:29:18,194 --> 00:29:19,112
A gang?

525
00:29:20,071 --> 00:29:21,531
I can't believe this.

526
00:29:24,450 --> 00:29:25,577
Oh my.

527
00:29:27,203 --> 00:29:30,498
I've… retired.

528
00:29:30,582 --> 00:29:33,459
But it's true you were in a gang.

529
00:29:33,543 --> 00:29:35,837
They say people never change.

530
00:29:35,920 --> 00:29:38,590
I'm so scared. I'm getting the chills.

531
00:29:38,673 --> 00:29:40,884
I can't believe there's a thug here.

532
00:29:40,967 --> 00:29:42,635
-Enough of that.
-Gosh.

533
00:29:42,719 --> 00:29:46,890
How would the residents trust you
to manage the apartment complex?

534
00:29:46,973 --> 00:29:50,476
How can a thug represent
the 9,800 households here?

535
00:29:50,560 --> 00:29:52,228
Withdraw your candidacy immediately!

536
00:29:52,312 --> 00:29:53,646
-Step down.
-Step down!

537
00:29:57,901 --> 00:29:59,068
Everyone!

538
00:30:00,403 --> 00:30:01,487
Calm down.

539
00:30:01,571 --> 00:30:04,782
Let's hear what he has to say first.

540
00:30:04,866 --> 00:30:08,161
I'm sure Mr. Park
would have had his own reasons.

541
00:30:08,244 --> 00:30:10,204
Right? Go on.

542
00:30:13,499 --> 00:30:15,793
Mr. Park?

543
00:30:15,877 --> 00:30:17,712
You should at least say something

544
00:30:17,795 --> 00:30:22,216
for us to know
whether or not this is true…

545
00:30:23,092 --> 00:30:24,052
First of all,

546
00:30:26,220 --> 00:30:28,222
I'm sorry for causing concern over this--

547
00:30:28,306 --> 00:30:29,849
Mr. Park.

548
00:30:29,933 --> 00:30:32,685
Please stand up and speak politely.

549
00:30:34,729 --> 00:30:36,272
Come on. Stand up.

550
00:30:36,356 --> 00:30:38,024
Stand up and talk.

551
00:30:40,526 --> 00:30:41,778
Stand up.

552
00:30:41,861 --> 00:30:44,822
Can't you hear me? Stand up.

553
00:30:54,832 --> 00:30:55,875
I…

554
00:30:56,584 --> 00:30:57,460
used to be

555
00:30:58,628 --> 00:31:00,004
in a gang,

556
00:31:01,673 --> 00:31:02,966
but that's in the past…

557
00:31:09,555 --> 00:31:10,723
-What?
-What's going on?

558
00:31:12,266 --> 00:31:14,435
What is it?

559
00:31:14,519 --> 00:31:17,271
The power suddenly went out. Hang on.

560
00:31:17,355 --> 00:31:18,398
Right.

561
00:31:18,481 --> 00:31:20,316
-Fix it.
-I think it's this.

562
00:31:20,400 --> 00:31:22,860
Then I guess we have no choice.

563
00:31:22,944 --> 00:31:27,407
Due to equipment issues,
we won't be able to broadcast the rest.

564
00:31:43,464 --> 00:31:44,799
Did you see the look on his face?

565
00:31:44,882 --> 00:31:47,010
He was as pale as a sheet.

566
00:31:47,969 --> 00:31:50,388
He'll have no choice but to withdraw.

567
00:31:50,471 --> 00:31:53,391
Withdrawing won't be the problem.
He'll have to move out.

568
00:31:54,058 --> 00:31:56,602
But why did you keep
such important information

569
00:31:56,686 --> 00:31:58,271
to yourself, sir?

570
00:31:58,354 --> 00:31:59,397
Right?

571
00:31:59,480 --> 00:32:00,940
If you'd told us in advance,

572
00:32:01,024 --> 00:32:03,693
we could've crushed him
on the spot back there.

573
00:32:04,444 --> 00:32:06,195
That was enough.

574
00:32:06,279 --> 00:32:08,156
He would have understood my words.

575
00:32:08,239 --> 00:32:11,451
You're just too generous, President Seo.

576
00:32:11,534 --> 00:32:12,660
How about a toast?

577
00:32:12,744 --> 00:32:14,620
-Cheers.
-Sure.

578
00:32:15,663 --> 00:32:17,832
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

579
00:32:18,833 --> 00:32:19,792
Bottoms up.

580
00:32:23,087 --> 00:32:24,005
We're screwed.

581
00:32:24,964 --> 00:32:25,798
We're screwed.

582
00:32:25,882 --> 00:32:26,966
Our gang…

583
00:32:27,050 --> 00:32:28,509
I mean, what do we do now?

584
00:32:28,593 --> 00:32:31,804
Since it's come to this,
can I just start packing?

585
00:32:31,888 --> 00:32:33,014
You little…

586
00:32:34,057 --> 00:32:35,058
Boss.

587
00:32:36,684 --> 00:32:38,478
Why couldn't you say anything?

588
00:32:38,561 --> 00:32:40,897
Why couldn't you say
that you're just an ordinary guy now

589
00:32:40,980 --> 00:32:42,273
who wants to be the president?

590
00:32:42,356 --> 00:32:43,608
I didn't have the chance to.

591
00:32:43,691 --> 00:32:45,902
Still, you could've just denied--

592
00:32:45,985 --> 00:32:48,071
You should've just denied it.

593
00:32:48,154 --> 00:32:50,156
-Then we can announce--
-No.

594
00:32:50,239 --> 00:32:52,450
Don't you want to be the president?

595
00:32:52,533 --> 00:32:54,786
There's no rule that says
you can't be the president

596
00:32:54,869 --> 00:32:55,953
if you were in a gang.

597
00:32:56,037 --> 00:32:58,039
And leaking private info
can land you two years

598
00:32:58,122 --> 00:32:59,582
or a fine of five million.

599
00:32:59,665 --> 00:33:01,292
Anyway, let's sue him first.

600
00:33:01,375 --> 00:33:03,419
Let's sue him!

601
00:33:03,503 --> 00:33:04,921
Ms. Kang, calm down…

602
00:33:05,004 --> 00:33:07,131
How can I calm down right now?

603
00:33:07,215 --> 00:33:08,174
Aren't you even angry?

604
00:33:08,257 --> 00:33:10,676
How dare they do this
in front of everyone?

605
00:33:11,344 --> 00:33:12,762
Ms. Kang.

606
00:33:15,473 --> 00:33:17,767
You guys,
look into how President Seo found out.

607
00:33:17,850 --> 00:33:19,185
-Yes, Boss.
-Yes, Boss.

608
00:33:19,769 --> 00:33:21,521
You passed the criminal background check,

609
00:33:21,604 --> 00:33:24,482
so they can't revoke your candidacy
just because they want to.

610
00:33:24,565 --> 00:33:26,359
The problem is public opinion.

611
00:33:29,529 --> 00:33:31,823
-He was in a gang.
-That kick.

612
00:33:31,906 --> 00:33:33,074
-He kicked him…
-A gang.

613
00:33:35,076 --> 00:33:36,494
Hello.

614
00:33:37,829 --> 00:33:38,704
Hi.

615
00:33:58,641 --> 00:34:00,059
I forgot my wallet!

616
00:34:00,143 --> 00:34:02,353
-She has a stomachache.
-I forgot my phone.

617
00:34:02,436 --> 00:34:03,980
-I forgot my laundry.
-Me too.

618
00:34:06,149 --> 00:34:07,150
But it's the fifth floor.

619
00:34:08,067 --> 00:34:09,986
-What? I can't believe it.
-Seriously.

620
00:34:11,195 --> 00:34:12,572
Goodness!

621
00:34:13,781 --> 00:34:15,825
Public opinion really is scary.

622
00:34:16,868 --> 00:34:18,077
I knew this would happen.

623
00:34:20,705 --> 00:34:22,206
Hello.

624
00:34:23,291 --> 00:34:25,001
Could I sit here?

625
00:34:26,085 --> 00:34:27,253
Yes, sure.

626
00:34:29,380 --> 00:34:31,507
-It's not like she did anything wrong.
-Right.

627
00:34:31,591 --> 00:34:33,885
Love isn't a sin.

628
00:34:35,136 --> 00:34:38,139
But did you know when you married him?

629
00:34:38,222 --> 00:34:40,349
Were you deceived, by any chance?

630
00:34:40,433 --> 00:34:41,976
-What?
-He doesn't…

631
00:34:42,059 --> 00:34:43,603
beat you or anything, does he?

632
00:34:43,686 --> 00:34:46,189
Oh, gosh. Then he'd be a real scumbag.

633
00:34:46,272 --> 00:34:47,857
That's crazy.

634
00:34:47,940 --> 00:34:50,276
That explains that kick.

635
00:34:50,359 --> 00:34:52,361
Right. He didn't seem
like an ordinary guy.

636
00:34:52,445 --> 00:34:54,280
What a waste of a handsome face.

637
00:34:54,363 --> 00:34:56,365
Why did he live like that
with such good looks?

638
00:34:56,449 --> 00:34:58,117
-Right?
-A gang? Seriously?

639
00:34:58,201 --> 00:34:59,827
-Hang on…
-Right.

640
00:35:00,411 --> 00:35:01,621
You should get divorced.

641
00:35:01,704 --> 00:35:03,497
-That's the only way.
-She's right.

642
00:35:05,082 --> 00:35:05,917
I…

643
00:35:06,459 --> 00:35:09,128
love his past as well.

644
00:35:09,212 --> 00:35:10,213
You know,

645
00:35:10,296 --> 00:35:12,506
someone's past isn't what's important.

646
00:35:12,590 --> 00:35:15,301
It's how you overcome your past
and live in the present.

647
00:35:15,885 --> 00:35:18,095
He doesn't do stuff like that anymore.

648
00:35:18,179 --> 00:35:20,598
He's responsible,
family-oriented, hardworking,

649
00:35:20,681 --> 00:35:21,849
and handsome.

650
00:35:21,933 --> 00:35:22,934
Right.

651
00:35:23,017 --> 00:35:25,228
He's the perfect husband.

652
00:35:25,728 --> 00:35:27,605
We were just worried about you, is all.

653
00:35:27,688 --> 00:35:29,690
There's no need to worry.

654
00:35:29,774 --> 00:35:32,735
I'll stand by my decision
until the very end.

655
00:35:32,818 --> 00:35:35,696
I chose him, and we're doing our best.

656
00:35:36,906 --> 00:35:39,367
Don't be quick to judge people
who are working hard.

657
00:35:40,117 --> 00:35:40,952
By the way,

658
00:35:41,035 --> 00:35:43,454
I married him
because I fell for his awesome kicks.

659
00:35:43,537 --> 00:35:44,372
My goodness.

660
00:35:48,668 --> 00:35:50,753
-They really are a couple.
-They're so alike.

661
00:35:55,925 --> 00:35:57,468
What was that?

662
00:35:57,551 --> 00:36:01,180
Did I just defend Park Hae-kang
because we're a family, even if it's fake?

663
00:36:03,432 --> 00:36:04,475
Unbelievable.

664
00:36:07,019 --> 00:36:08,604
Someone's coming, Boss!

665
00:36:10,273 --> 00:36:12,566
Hello. Let me take that for you.

666
00:36:12,650 --> 00:36:14,819
It's fine. I can do it.

667
00:36:14,902 --> 00:36:16,445
-I'll do it.
-No, it's fine.

668
00:36:18,906 --> 00:36:20,408
Let me take that.

669
00:36:22,201 --> 00:36:23,035
All right.

670
00:36:26,789 --> 00:36:28,374
-Have a nice day.
-Thank you.

671
00:36:47,310 --> 00:36:48,853
You know,

672
00:36:48,936 --> 00:36:51,105
if you make others suffer,

673
00:36:52,023 --> 00:36:54,317
it'll come back to haunt you.

674
00:36:55,484 --> 00:36:56,319
Me?

675
00:36:58,696 --> 00:37:00,364
-What are you talking about?
-It was you.

676
00:37:00,448 --> 00:37:01,782
What do you mean?

677
00:37:02,450 --> 00:37:05,494
You're the one who uploaded
that post about academic fraud.

678
00:37:07,621 --> 00:37:11,834
You're the one
who lied about the deliveries first.

679
00:37:11,917 --> 00:37:14,128
I really did graduate
from Ilhwa Women's University

680
00:37:14,211 --> 00:37:15,671
at the top of my class.

681
00:37:15,755 --> 00:37:17,590
And I really worked hard to deliver…

682
00:37:22,345 --> 00:37:24,388
You can't defeat President Seo
at this rate.

683
00:37:24,472 --> 00:37:26,849
Elections are all about public opinion.

684
00:37:26,932 --> 00:37:29,518
But you've already lost there,
like I have.

685
00:37:29,602 --> 00:37:31,228
Serves you right.

686
00:37:32,897 --> 00:37:35,066
You really are frustrating.

687
00:37:36,233 --> 00:37:37,443
What do you mean?

688
00:37:37,526 --> 00:37:40,946
You have no idea
how much President Seo and his cronies

689
00:37:41,030 --> 00:37:43,741
ruined our apartment complex
and how much they pocketed.

690
00:37:44,950 --> 00:37:47,411
I can't stand to see them
continue on like this.

691
00:37:47,495 --> 00:37:49,080
This is so frustrating.

692
00:37:49,163 --> 00:37:51,123
But it's not like I can trust you either.

693
00:37:53,834 --> 00:37:54,710
Let's go.

694
00:37:55,544 --> 00:37:56,504
Where?

695
00:37:56,587 --> 00:37:57,880
Will you do nothing, then?

696
00:37:57,963 --> 00:37:59,673
You have to at least try something.

697
00:37:59,757 --> 00:38:01,801
Where's your fighting spirit?

698
00:38:02,468 --> 00:38:03,803
Follow me. Come on.

699
00:38:07,181 --> 00:38:08,557
Follow me.

700
00:38:09,225 --> 00:38:10,935
It's not anywhere bad. Come on.

701
00:38:16,857 --> 00:38:20,319
Move Oman Station Line 10, Exit 3

702
00:38:20,403 --> 00:38:22,238
to True Value State!

703
00:38:22,321 --> 00:38:25,157
-Move Exit 3 to True Value State!
-Move Exit 3 to True Value State!

704
00:38:25,241 --> 00:38:27,952
Withdraw the Oman Station

705
00:38:28,035 --> 00:38:30,037
exit announcement!

706
00:38:30,121 --> 00:38:33,958
-Withdraw the announcement!
-Withdraw the announcement!

707
00:38:34,041 --> 00:38:37,545
-Withdraw the announcement!
-Withdraw the announcement!

708
00:38:37,628 --> 00:38:39,588
True Value!

709
00:38:39,672 --> 00:38:44,677
-True Value!
-True Value!

710
00:38:44,760 --> 00:38:47,054
What am I even doing here?

711
00:38:47,138 --> 00:38:51,183
-Exit 3!
-Exit 3!

712
00:38:51,267 --> 00:38:52,351
MOVE EXIT 3 TO TRUE VALUE

713
00:38:53,477 --> 00:38:55,354
This looks delicious.

714
00:38:55,438 --> 00:38:58,149
It was tough protesting
in such cold weather, wasn't it?

715
00:38:58,232 --> 00:39:00,901
Since we had a new member join us today,

716
00:39:00,985 --> 00:39:02,445
I'm treating everyone.

717
00:39:02,528 --> 00:39:03,821
Enjoy.

718
00:39:03,904 --> 00:39:05,156
You're paying again?

719
00:39:05,239 --> 00:39:06,699
Let's just split the bill.

720
00:39:06,782 --> 00:39:08,659
Don't say that.

721
00:39:08,742 --> 00:39:09,827
Come on.

722
00:39:09,910 --> 00:39:12,746
Once the exit is built
right in front of our apartment complex,

723
00:39:12,830 --> 00:39:14,498
housing prices will go through the roof.

724
00:39:14,582 --> 00:39:18,502
Jang Suk-jin from True Value
can pay for this much. Right?

725
00:39:18,586 --> 00:39:20,045
All right, fine.

726
00:39:20,129 --> 00:39:21,630
Eat up, everyone.

727
00:39:21,714 --> 00:39:22,756
Okay.

728
00:39:22,840 --> 00:39:25,509
Why is Ms. Park calling me again?

729
00:39:25,593 --> 00:39:27,761
Let me take this call. Eat up, everyone.

730
00:39:27,845 --> 00:39:29,013
-Thanks.
-Sure.

731
00:39:29,096 --> 00:39:31,724
-Enjoy.
-Hello, it's Jang Suk-jin.

732
00:39:31,807 --> 00:39:32,933
Yes.

733
00:39:33,017 --> 00:39:34,810
Why am I eating this right now?

734
00:39:34,894 --> 00:39:37,980
Excuse me.
It's my first time joining the protest.

735
00:39:38,063 --> 00:39:41,066
Is it really possible that the subway exit

736
00:39:41,150 --> 00:39:43,652
will be moved to True Value instead?

737
00:39:44,862 --> 00:39:45,946
No.

738
00:39:47,323 --> 00:39:49,325
Then why are we doing this?

739
00:39:50,951 --> 00:39:52,119
It's fun.

740
00:39:52,953 --> 00:39:54,788
We get to hang out and eat together.

741
00:39:55,748 --> 00:39:56,832
Oh, stop.

742
00:39:56,916 --> 00:39:58,209
Welcome.

743
00:39:58,709 --> 00:40:03,005
Well, unless some kind of cultural relic
is dug up in Oman New Town,

744
00:40:03,088 --> 00:40:05,049
a finalized plan
wouldn't be changed that easily…

745
00:40:05,132 --> 00:40:06,091
Relic?

746
00:40:13,807 --> 00:40:16,644
Relics were once discovered in Busan

747
00:40:16,727 --> 00:40:18,729
during subway construction,

748
00:40:18,812 --> 00:40:22,274
so new town projects
ended up being canceled or delayed.

749
00:40:22,983 --> 00:40:25,152
Anyway, they need to discover some relics.

750
00:40:32,368 --> 00:40:33,577
No, not you.

751
00:40:34,537 --> 00:40:36,580
-Is something going on?
-You two.

752
00:40:36,664 --> 00:40:38,791
You need to go to Japan immediately.

753
00:40:38,874 --> 00:40:40,167
-What?
-Japan?

754
00:40:40,251 --> 00:40:41,293
Yes.

755
00:40:56,934 --> 00:40:57,935
Long time no see.

756
00:40:58,018 --> 00:40:59,436
Long time no see.

757
00:41:00,271 --> 00:41:01,355
-Hello.
-Hi.

758
00:41:01,438 --> 00:41:02,314
Hi. This way, please.

759
00:41:22,042 --> 00:41:23,377
Sir, we're connected.

760
00:41:25,421 --> 00:41:27,131
-Boss.
-Okay. I can see you.

761
00:41:32,136 --> 00:41:34,096
It's been a while, Park Hae-kang.

762
00:41:34,972 --> 00:41:36,432
Explain to me

763
00:41:37,474 --> 00:41:38,767
what's going on right now.

764
00:41:38,851 --> 00:41:40,728
I'll keep it simple.

765
00:41:40,811 --> 00:41:42,605
We're brothers, aren't we?

766
00:41:42,688 --> 00:41:44,064
Though I, Tadayoshi,

767
00:41:44,148 --> 00:41:47,067
do not share blood with you,
Park Hae-kang,

768
00:41:47,151 --> 00:41:48,861
you are my brother

769
00:41:49,987 --> 00:41:51,405
whom I swore to protect.

770
00:41:54,450 --> 00:41:57,286
I will give you a chance
to repay that debt.

771
00:41:58,037 --> 00:42:01,081
I need your help this time.

772
00:42:01,707 --> 00:42:03,208
Anything you say.

773
00:42:03,792 --> 00:42:05,044
Who do you want dead?

774
00:42:05,628 --> 00:42:07,838
The Korean relic you have…

775
00:42:08,547 --> 00:42:09,965
I need it.

776
00:42:18,599 --> 00:42:19,975
This jerk.

777
00:42:20,059 --> 00:42:21,185
Tadayoshi.

778
00:42:21,769 --> 00:42:23,187
The real one, not a fake one.

779
00:42:23,270 --> 00:42:25,773
Brothers shouldn't
deceive each other like this.

780
00:42:30,944 --> 00:42:34,948
You truly do deserve to be my brother.

781
00:42:38,786 --> 00:42:40,120
What? Where's he…

782
00:42:46,669 --> 00:42:47,920
-My leg. Boss.
-Boss.

783
00:42:48,003 --> 00:42:50,214
Tadayoshi just left. What's going on?

784
00:42:54,760 --> 00:42:57,096
Boss, how did you know this was a fake?

785
00:42:57,179 --> 00:42:58,931
He brought that in with his bare hands.

786
00:42:59,014 --> 00:43:00,015
But look now.

787
00:43:00,099 --> 00:43:02,226
He's carrying that one with gloves.

788
00:43:12,569 --> 00:43:13,696
Tadayoshi.

789
00:43:28,919 --> 00:43:30,087
Hello.

790
00:43:30,170 --> 00:43:31,880
-Hello.
-Hello.

791
00:43:34,842 --> 00:43:36,593
I knew it.

792
00:43:36,677 --> 00:43:38,512
Young people lack perseverance.

793
00:43:43,392 --> 00:43:44,393
-Hello.
-Hello.

794
00:43:44,476 --> 00:43:46,145
-You went out this morning?
-Yes.

795
00:43:46,228 --> 00:43:47,312
-See you around.
-Ma'am.

796
00:43:47,396 --> 00:43:48,689
-Gosh!
-What took you so long?

797
00:43:48,772 --> 00:43:50,441
I've been waiting for you.

798
00:43:50,524 --> 00:43:53,861
You weren't over there, so…

799
00:43:53,944 --> 00:43:55,696
Fine. Just look at me.

800
00:43:55,779 --> 00:43:56,739
Look at me.

801
00:43:56,822 --> 00:43:58,365
-What's this about?
-Look at me.

802
00:43:58,449 --> 00:44:00,242
All right. Ta-da.

803
00:44:00,325 --> 00:44:02,494
Ms. Jang Suk-jin…

804
00:44:02,578 --> 00:44:03,746
-Welcome!
-Welcome!

805
00:44:03,829 --> 00:44:05,414
-Welcome!
-Welcome!

806
00:44:05,998 --> 00:44:06,832
Goodness.

807
00:44:07,791 --> 00:44:08,917
What is this?

808
00:44:09,001 --> 00:44:12,421
Move Oman Station
Line 10, Exit 3 to True Value!

809
00:44:12,504 --> 00:44:14,715
-True Value!
-True Value!

810
00:44:14,798 --> 00:44:17,342
Withdraw the decision
that ignored the residents' voices!

811
00:44:17,426 --> 00:44:19,803
-Withdraw the decision!
-Withdraw the decision!

812
00:44:21,847 --> 00:44:23,807
-You're here.
-What's going on here?

813
00:44:23,891 --> 00:44:26,602
I don't know.
How did you know we were doing this?

814
00:44:26,685 --> 00:44:28,979
I told them to come here.

815
00:44:29,062 --> 00:44:31,315
-My gosh.
-Thank you all for coming.

816
00:44:31,398 --> 00:44:33,108
Here. Pass these around

817
00:44:33,192 --> 00:44:35,319
and distribute them to passersby.

818
00:44:35,402 --> 00:44:37,070
Let's do this.

819
00:44:37,154 --> 00:44:38,238
This way.

820
00:44:41,992 --> 00:44:44,453
Move Oman Station
Line 10, Exit 3 to True Value!

821
00:44:44,536 --> 00:44:46,288
-True Value!
-True Value!

822
00:44:46,371 --> 00:44:49,124
Withdraw the decision
that ignored the residents' voices!

823
00:44:49,208 --> 00:44:51,043
-Withdraw the decision!
-Withdraw the decision!

824
00:44:55,047 --> 00:44:57,966
Withdraw the decision
that ignored the residents' voices!

825
00:45:08,602 --> 00:45:11,605
-Park Hae-kang leads us to victory!
-Park Hae-kang leads us to victory!

826
00:45:13,273 --> 00:45:14,858
-Park Hae-kang!
-Park Hae-kang!

827
00:45:14,942 --> 00:45:17,903
Move Exit 3 to True Value!

828
00:45:17,986 --> 00:45:20,614
-True Value!
-True Value!

829
00:45:20,697 --> 00:45:22,241
Do you need anything else?

830
00:45:22,324 --> 00:45:23,742
No, thank you.

831
00:45:23,825 --> 00:45:25,619
-Mr. Park!
-Yes?

832
00:45:25,702 --> 00:45:28,622
We need more gimbap here!

833
00:45:28,705 --> 00:45:30,040
Coming!

834
00:45:32,626 --> 00:45:33,710
There's some here.

835
00:45:39,216 --> 00:45:40,801
-This is good.
-Thank you.

836
00:45:40,884 --> 00:45:42,844
-Is it good?
-Is it good?

837
00:45:53,272 --> 00:45:54,523
Oh, gosh!

838
00:45:57,568 --> 00:45:58,735
My goodness.

839
00:45:58,819 --> 00:46:00,487
Why did you fall?

840
00:46:01,154 --> 00:46:02,155
He fell!

841
00:46:02,239 --> 00:46:03,490
Are you okay?

842
00:46:04,491 --> 00:46:05,826
Are you hurt?

843
00:46:05,909 --> 00:46:08,203
Yes. But what is that?

844
00:46:08,287 --> 00:46:09,788
What did I trip on?

845
00:46:10,622 --> 00:46:13,125
Gosh, it must have been this.

846
00:46:14,001 --> 00:46:15,043
What is that?

847
00:46:15,127 --> 00:46:16,128
What is this?

848
00:46:16,712 --> 00:46:19,172
Goodness…

849
00:46:22,926 --> 00:46:23,760
What is this?

850
00:46:24,761 --> 00:46:26,513
It looks like they found something.

851
00:46:30,559 --> 00:46:31,476
Wait…

852
00:46:33,478 --> 00:46:35,564
It looks really old.

853
00:46:36,315 --> 00:46:37,733
What is this?

854
00:46:37,816 --> 00:46:39,359
-It looks like some kind of relic.
-Relic?

855
00:46:39,443 --> 00:46:41,403
-We found a relic?
-A relic?

856
00:46:41,486 --> 00:46:42,654
-A relic!
-A relic!

857
00:46:45,949 --> 00:46:48,827
They must have found a relic!

858
00:46:48,910 --> 00:46:49,953
Mr. Park.

859
00:46:50,621 --> 00:46:53,498
Something incredible has just happened.

860
00:46:54,583 --> 00:46:59,254
Everyone! Report this to the media!

861
00:46:59,338 --> 00:47:00,380
Hurry! Report this!

862
00:47:00,464 --> 00:47:02,382
Our house prices are going to soar!

863
00:47:16,021 --> 00:47:19,232
I think we've dug quite a bit.
Do we dig more?

864
00:47:19,316 --> 00:47:20,525
Dig the deepest over there.

865
00:47:21,693 --> 00:47:24,237
Make the depths different
so they'll keep getting discovered.

866
00:47:24,321 --> 00:47:26,740
Mr. Park, why don't I

867
00:47:26,823 --> 00:47:30,160
just get a good price for this
from a fence I know?

868
00:47:30,243 --> 00:47:31,536
We can use the money…

869
00:47:31,620 --> 00:47:32,788
Should I bury you in there?

870
00:47:36,667 --> 00:47:37,876
Boss.

871
00:47:39,044 --> 00:47:40,671
Will this really work, though?

872
00:47:40,754 --> 00:47:42,923
If apartment prices soar
after they're discovered,

873
00:47:43,006 --> 00:47:45,467
everyone will forget
that I used to be in a gang.

874
00:47:45,550 --> 00:47:48,637
I'll just be the guy
who helped raise the apartment prices.

875
00:47:48,720 --> 00:47:52,224
This is the only thing
that can flip public opinion about me

876
00:47:52,307 --> 00:47:53,809
in one shot.

877
00:47:53,892 --> 00:47:55,352
-So dig.
-Yes, Boss!

878
00:47:55,435 --> 00:47:56,478
-Yes, Boss!
-Yes, Boss!

879
00:47:56,561 --> 00:47:57,646
Yes, sir!

880
00:47:58,146 --> 00:48:00,732
-Let's dig.
-Let's dig.

881
00:48:00,816 --> 00:48:03,193
-Let's dig.
-Let's dig.

882
00:48:11,284 --> 00:48:12,661
JOEUN REAL ESTATE

883
00:48:12,744 --> 00:48:13,745
They discovered relics.

884
00:48:13,829 --> 00:48:15,914
They'll reconsider the subway exit.

885
00:48:15,997 --> 00:48:20,210
Of course. They have no choice
but to change it to True Value.

886
00:48:20,293 --> 00:48:22,713
Today is the cheapest it'll ever be.

887
00:48:22,796 --> 00:48:24,548
-Oman New Town…
-They found relics.

888
00:48:24,631 --> 00:48:26,550
So development will be put to a stop.

889
00:48:26,633 --> 00:48:29,219
The probability of the exit
being changed to True Value is…

890
00:48:29,302 --> 00:48:30,887
-90%.
-90%.

891
00:48:32,931 --> 00:48:34,224
It's starting.

892
00:48:37,102 --> 00:48:41,440
A variety of artifacts, such as pottery,
iron swords, and arrowheads,

893
00:48:41,523 --> 00:48:43,442
have been excavated
from the Oman New Town site.

894
00:48:43,525 --> 00:48:46,361
The discovery was made in an area
with no prior historical research,

895
00:48:46,445 --> 00:48:49,156
so historians are also deeply confused.

896
00:48:49,239 --> 00:48:52,951
Even in our field,
this is an unexpected find.

897
00:48:53,034 --> 00:48:56,079
Through a full investigation of the site,
we'll be able to determine

898
00:48:56,163 --> 00:48:59,833
the historical relationship
between the finds and the location.

899
00:48:59,916 --> 00:49:01,001
I was just walking by…

900
00:49:01,084 --> 00:49:02,294
It's him!

901
00:49:02,377 --> 00:49:04,713
I just tripped on something
and fell like this.

902
00:49:04,796 --> 00:49:07,132
That relic was just buried right there.

903
00:49:08,175 --> 00:49:10,552
With the unexpected discovery
of the cultural artifact,

904
00:49:10,635 --> 00:49:13,597
the new town development
is expected to be put on hold for now,

905
00:49:13,680 --> 00:49:18,685
and the subway exit for Oman Station,
Line 10, is likely to be reconsidered.

906
00:49:23,774 --> 00:49:26,193
How on earth did you discover that
at just the right time?

907
00:49:26,276 --> 00:49:28,737
I guess I can say I was lucky.

908
00:49:30,071 --> 00:49:32,073
He made that luck.

909
00:49:33,617 --> 00:49:34,534
Lizard.

910
00:49:35,202 --> 00:49:39,080
I mean, heaven helps
those who help themselves,

911
00:49:39,164 --> 00:49:40,874
so I guess the earth

912
00:49:42,083 --> 00:49:44,085
also created that for you.

913
00:49:44,169 --> 00:49:46,546
That's what I meant.

914
00:49:47,672 --> 00:49:49,257
Anyway, congratulations.

915
00:49:49,341 --> 00:49:51,551
You might actually become
the president at this rate.

916
00:49:51,635 --> 00:49:54,679
Boss, the apartment complex forum
is filled with comments about you.

917
00:49:54,763 --> 00:49:56,056
Let me see.

918
00:49:57,015 --> 00:50:00,310
"The true hero who saved True Value,
Park Hae-kang."

919
00:50:00,393 --> 00:50:02,354
"Park Hae-kang is better than my own son."

920
00:50:02,437 --> 00:50:05,524
"The next residents' association president
should be Park Hae-kang."

921
00:50:06,525 --> 00:50:08,902
You've truly become
the hottest guy in True Value.

922
00:50:08,985 --> 00:50:10,195
He's like a celebrity!

923
00:50:12,989 --> 00:50:15,450
Stop spilling crumbs while eating snacks.

924
00:50:15,534 --> 00:50:17,661
Why do I always have
to clean up after you?

925
00:50:18,370 --> 00:50:21,122
We're going to have cockroaches in here
because of you!

926
00:50:21,623 --> 00:50:24,543
I applaud you all

927
00:50:24,626 --> 00:50:28,255
for working so hard.

928
00:50:28,338 --> 00:50:30,382
Cheers!

929
00:50:30,465 --> 00:50:32,926
-Cheers!
-Cheers!

930
00:50:39,474 --> 00:50:43,061
The heavens have answered our prayers,
don't you think?

931
00:50:43,144 --> 00:50:46,606
If you hadn't suggested protesting,
this would never have happened.

932
00:50:46,690 --> 00:50:49,860
Right. Mr. Park should know
that it was all thanks to you.

933
00:50:49,943 --> 00:50:51,486
I'm sure he knows.

934
00:50:51,570 --> 00:50:53,113
Eat up, everyone.

935
00:50:53,864 --> 00:50:55,240
Enjoy.

936
00:50:55,323 --> 00:50:57,117
My son.

937
00:50:57,200 --> 00:50:58,118
You're home.

938
00:50:58,201 --> 00:50:59,035
Hello.

939
00:50:59,119 --> 00:51:01,913
I'm in a great mood today.

940
00:51:01,997 --> 00:51:07,627
Our apartment prices have soared.

941
00:51:07,711 --> 00:51:08,712
Have some meat.

942
00:51:08,795 --> 00:51:09,754
-Come here.
-Sit.

943
00:51:09,838 --> 00:51:11,506
It's fine. Enjoy your dinner.

944
00:51:11,590 --> 00:51:12,966
Gosh.

945
00:51:13,758 --> 00:51:15,552
He's really shy.

946
00:51:15,635 --> 00:51:17,178
Kids these days are so shy.

947
00:51:20,390 --> 00:51:22,767
Development is going to be put on hold

948
00:51:23,351 --> 00:51:25,395
until the excavation
and investigation are complete

949
00:51:26,021 --> 00:51:27,314
because of the relics.

950
00:51:28,356 --> 00:51:30,567
I checked the relevant laws and past cases

951
00:51:30,650 --> 00:51:32,569
on buried cultural assets,

952
00:51:32,652 --> 00:51:36,239
but there's nothing we can really do
for the next three years.

953
00:51:43,830 --> 00:51:45,624
I guess I can't fit…

954
00:51:48,752 --> 00:51:50,545
the last piece of my puzzle.

955
00:52:15,195 --> 00:52:18,531
Why did they have to find
a damn relic over there?

956
00:52:18,615 --> 00:52:21,159
I can't believe this.

957
00:52:21,242 --> 00:52:22,786
This is driving me crazy.

958
00:52:22,869 --> 00:52:24,621
What should we do?

959
00:52:24,704 --> 00:52:27,332
The subway exit
is likely to be moved to True Value now.

960
00:52:27,415 --> 00:52:31,002
Everyone's talking about Park Hae-kang
being the president because of this.

961
00:52:31,086 --> 00:52:33,171
They're not even bringing
up the gang anymore.

962
00:52:33,254 --> 00:52:37,300
They were the ones saying
a former thug couldn't be the president.

963
00:52:37,384 --> 00:52:39,803
Look how fickle they are.

964
00:52:41,805 --> 00:52:43,431
The election is tomorrow.

965
00:52:44,349 --> 00:52:48,311
Park Hae-kang might actually
become the president at this rate.

966
00:52:49,104 --> 00:52:51,564
Why would you say that?

967
00:52:51,648 --> 00:52:53,566
You'll just bring bad luck by saying that!

968
00:52:53,650 --> 00:52:57,153
Park Hae-kang can never
become the president. Never!

969
00:52:59,239 --> 00:53:02,242
Get out, all of you!

970
00:53:02,325 --> 00:53:03,451
Bye, sir.

971
00:53:07,831 --> 00:53:09,833
DAY OF THE PRESIDENT ELECTION

972
00:53:09,916 --> 00:53:12,210
4TH-TERM RESIDENTS' ASSOCIATION
PRESIDENT ELECTION

973
00:53:12,293 --> 00:53:13,962
1 SEO GANG-WON, 2 PARK HAE-KANG

974
00:53:17,841 --> 00:53:18,800
BALLOT DISTRIBUTION

975
00:53:27,058 --> 00:53:30,854
CANDIDATE 2, PARK HAE-KANG

976
00:53:30,937 --> 00:53:32,814
BALLOT

977
00:53:33,523 --> 00:53:34,691
All right.

978
00:53:34,774 --> 00:53:36,651
Don't drop the ballot yet.

979
00:53:36,735 --> 00:53:38,778
Smile a little more, please.

980
00:53:40,030 --> 00:53:45,910
CANDIDATE 1, SEO GANG-WON

981
00:53:45,994 --> 00:53:47,537
VOTING BOX
SEO GANG-WON

982
00:54:26,242 --> 00:54:27,702
It's 6:00, Boss.

983
00:54:28,953 --> 00:54:29,913
Is it posted?

984
00:54:31,122 --> 00:54:32,957
This is the management office.

985
00:54:33,041 --> 00:54:36,503
We would like to inform you
that Park Hae-kang from District 4

986
00:54:36,586 --> 00:54:40,215
has been elected as the new
residents' association president.

987
00:54:40,298 --> 00:54:41,132
Yes!

988
00:54:50,600 --> 00:54:51,518
Thank you.

989
00:54:51,601 --> 00:54:53,812
Congratulations.

990
00:54:54,562 --> 00:54:55,730
You did it, Boss!

991
00:54:55,814 --> 00:54:57,524
-You did it!
-We did it!

992
00:54:58,108 --> 00:54:59,359
Congratulations, Mr. Park.

993
00:54:59,442 --> 00:55:02,737
You finally got the position
that you wanted so badly.

994
00:55:03,279 --> 00:55:04,447
It's all thanks to you.

995
00:55:05,073 --> 00:55:06,741
Is my job over now, then?

996
00:55:06,825 --> 00:55:08,368
Well,

997
00:55:08,451 --> 00:55:10,328
wouldn't people think it strange

998
00:55:10,411 --> 00:55:12,330
if my wife suddenly disappeared?

999
00:55:12,413 --> 00:55:15,834
Why don't you work
for about two more weeks?

1000
00:55:16,543 --> 00:55:19,295
Well, if you pay me for the extra days,

1001
00:55:19,379 --> 00:55:20,797
that won't be difficult.

1002
00:55:20,880 --> 00:55:23,216
Of course, you'll be paid for it.

1003
00:55:24,425 --> 00:55:26,261
Ms. Kang, we should throw a party today.

1004
00:55:26,344 --> 00:55:28,513
I'll make an amazing dinner tonight.

1005
00:55:28,596 --> 00:55:29,889
Join us if you have time.

1006
00:55:29,973 --> 00:55:31,516
Yes, sure.

1007
00:55:32,016 --> 00:55:34,144
Don't cook.
Just order everything you want to eat.

1008
00:55:37,480 --> 00:55:40,441
Sorry, but can you give me an autograph?

1009
00:55:40,525 --> 00:55:43,736
Shouldn't we have some drinks
to celebrate tonight?

1010
00:55:44,320 --> 00:55:45,613
I'll go buy the drinks.

1011
00:55:46,573 --> 00:55:47,866
We can't send you out for that.

1012
00:55:47,949 --> 00:55:48,908
Thank you.

1013
00:55:50,952 --> 00:55:53,788
The leading intellectual of our time,
Park Hae-kang.

1014
00:56:01,963 --> 00:56:04,048
RESIDENTS' ASSOCIATION PRESIDENT'S OFFICE

1015
00:56:09,179 --> 00:56:10,263
Ta-da.

1016
00:56:13,808 --> 00:56:14,684
Sir.

1017
00:56:18,438 --> 00:56:20,565
A historic turnout

1018
00:56:21,608 --> 00:56:23,860
of 74%,

1019
00:56:23,943 --> 00:56:28,031
and an overwhelming 90% of the vote.

1020
00:56:28,114 --> 00:56:30,992
While Park Hae-kang achieved all of this,

1021
00:56:31,075 --> 00:56:33,953
what exactly were you doing?

1022
00:56:35,288 --> 00:56:37,040
I'm really sorry,

1023
00:56:37,123 --> 00:56:39,834
but I believe

1024
00:56:39,918 --> 00:56:41,211
I can flip the results.

1025
00:56:41,294 --> 00:56:43,171
So if you trust me, I'll…

1026
00:56:43,254 --> 00:56:44,547
No.

1027
00:56:45,673 --> 00:56:46,591
I…

1028
00:56:47,091 --> 00:56:50,720
can't stand those who take my money

1029
00:56:50,803 --> 00:56:54,057
and don't do their job.

1030
00:56:58,353 --> 00:56:59,270
Sir.

1031
00:57:01,314 --> 00:57:03,358
I'm really sorry.

1032
00:57:03,441 --> 00:57:06,236
But honestly, don't you think

1033
00:57:06,319 --> 00:57:09,155
I've been doing a good job so far?

1034
00:57:09,239 --> 00:57:11,324
Sir, please…

1035
00:57:11,407 --> 00:57:13,034
Mr. Lee!

1036
00:57:13,117 --> 00:57:14,661
Sir, please…

1037
00:57:14,744 --> 00:57:16,412
Please give me another chance.

1038
00:57:16,496 --> 00:57:18,248
Mr. Lee…

1039
00:57:19,874 --> 00:57:21,751
You won't need this anymore.

1040
00:57:21,834 --> 00:57:23,211
Just one more chance…

1041
00:57:35,390 --> 00:57:36,599
How do you like that?

1042
00:57:49,654 --> 00:57:50,655
Hello.

1043
00:57:52,323 --> 00:57:53,449
Mr. Park.

1044
00:57:54,450 --> 00:57:55,326
Well…

1045
00:57:56,828 --> 00:57:58,413
I heard the good news.

1046
00:57:59,080 --> 00:57:59,956
Congratulations.

1047
00:58:00,039 --> 00:58:01,624
You already heard?

1048
00:58:04,794 --> 00:58:05,628
Blood?

1049
00:58:16,306 --> 00:58:18,266
You must be on your way home from work.

1050
00:58:18,349 --> 00:58:20,685
I had some business
at the management office, and…

1051
00:58:28,151 --> 00:58:30,194
Well, goodnight.

1052
00:58:30,778 --> 00:58:31,863
Right.

1053
00:58:35,617 --> 00:58:36,951
Mr. Park.

1054
00:58:38,411 --> 00:58:39,370
Yes?

1055
00:58:42,290 --> 00:58:44,334
Congratulations

1056
00:58:45,918 --> 00:58:48,046
on being elected president.

1057
00:58:49,839 --> 00:58:51,591
Thank you.

1058
00:58:51,674 --> 00:58:52,884
Goodnight, then.

1059
00:58:53,968 --> 00:58:55,011
Mr. Park?

1060
00:58:55,970 --> 00:58:57,013
Yes?

1061
00:59:05,396 --> 00:59:06,522
We'll…

1062
00:59:07,649 --> 00:59:09,817
be seeing each other again.

1063
00:59:39,806 --> 00:59:42,558
THE APARTMENT JOB

1064
01:00:06,666 --> 01:00:08,209
But why is that guy going so far

1065
01:00:08,292 --> 01:00:11,170
as to fake a family to become
a residents' association president?

1066
01:00:11,254 --> 01:00:12,714
It's beautiful.

1067
01:00:12,797 --> 01:00:15,341
"Apartment complexes,
a hotbed of corruption!"

1068
01:00:15,425 --> 01:00:19,095
Not writing up contracts properly,
embezzling maintenance funds…

1069
01:00:19,178 --> 01:00:22,181
So please,
don't get involved in such corruption.

1070
01:00:22,265 --> 01:00:23,891
-Gyeong-nam, prepare a bag.
-Yes, sir.

1071
01:00:23,975 --> 01:00:26,352
-Big Guy, sell off everything in the home.
-Yes, sir.

1072
01:00:26,436 --> 01:00:28,479
Je-gil, get the facility manager's stamp.

1073
01:00:28,563 --> 01:00:30,064
"Power never lasts."

1074
01:00:30,148 --> 01:00:35,027
I'm offering to manage
your family risk for you.

1075
01:00:35,111 --> 01:00:38,197
It's almost impossible
for such relics to be found here.

1076
01:00:38,281 --> 01:00:40,825
So someone planted them on purpose?

1077
01:00:40,908 --> 01:00:42,827
If I catch whoever did this…

1078
01:00:42,910 --> 01:00:44,245
Ms. Kang.

1079
01:00:44,328 --> 01:00:45,913
I'm going to kill them.

1080
01:00:45,997 --> 01:00:48,750
We'll hit the bank in the morning,
get the money, and leave immediately.

1081
01:00:51,836 --> 01:00:53,838
Subtitle translation by: Juyoung Park

